column1: Eva has worked tirelessly to make sure that this election we delivered a victory for President-elect Joe Biden as well as our House Representatives and local candidates across this state.   RT to wish Eva a happy birthday and to thank her for all of her hard work.
Wishing the happiest of birthdays to Executive Director of the Maryland Democratic Party Eva Lewis! @mddems

Michael was a conservationist and wildlife expert who devoted his life to the community and as a public servant for nearly 40 years.   I know we are joined in our grief by countless others who knew and loved him too.
It is with a heavy heart that I share that Michael Baker a long-time and beloved Team Dutch family member has passed away. https://t.co/TAKh7WicHl

I couldn’t have done this without supporters like you. Whether you volunteered chipped in a few dollars or talked to your friends & family about our race I’m so grateful.  There are big issues facing us & now it’s time to get to work.
Thank you. I am honored & humbled to continue representing Maryland’s 2nd District in Congress & to keep fighting every day for the state I love.

#GOTV with @CalvinBallTeam & @CouncilmanOpelJ in Howard County today.  If you haven’t voted yet that should be at the top of your to-do list for today.   #VOTE & make your voice heard in this incredibly important election.  Find your polling place here >> https://t.co/ntw0s6mkci https://t.co/xNt3Qnlt64

If you haven’t voted yet you can find your polling place here >> https://t.co/AzlrBqpfDN  This election will come down to a matter of votes -- that’s why every single one matters. Make sure you make your voice heard and that your friends and family have a plan to #VOTE.
